### Backend API Tests for Task Analysis
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "test123"
}

### 2. Login with the user
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "test123"
}

### 3. Create a category (replace YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN with token from login)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN

{
  "name": "Work"
}

### 4. Get all categories
GET http://localhost:8080/api/categories
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN

### 5. Create a task
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN

{
  "name": "Test Task",
  "description": "This is a test task",
  "categoryId": 1,
  "subtaskCount": 3
}

### 6. Get all tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN

### 7. Start timer for subtask 1
POST http://localhost:8080/api/timer/start/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN

### 8. Stop timer for subtask 1
POST http://localhost:8080/api/timer/stop/1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN
